      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're probably looking for the most overused and tired stereotypes to subvert, but I'll give you some examples of the most common ones. \n\n- The \"angry black woman\" trope, where a black female character is portrayed as being overly aggressive or emotional, often used for comedic effect.\n- The \"model minority\" stereotype, where Asian characters are depicted as being overly successful and obedient, often to the point of being seen as unauthentic.\n- The \"lazy Latino\" stereotype, where Latino characters are portrayed as being lazy, unmotivated, and only good for manual labor.\n- The \"exotic other\" stereotype, where characters from non-white backgrounds are portrayed as being mysterious, exotic, and often eroticized.\n- The \"white savior complex\", where a white character is portrayed as being the only one who can save or rescue people of color.\n\nKeep in mind that these stereotypes are tired and have been used to marginalize and oppress people of color for far too long.",
